theorem closure_interior_eq_univ_of_dense_and_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hDense : Dense (A : Set X)) (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure (interior (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  classical
  -- From density of `A`, its closure is the whole space.
  have hClA : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    (Topology.dense_iff_closure_eq_univ).1 hDense
  -- `P1` gives `A ⊆ closure (interior A)`, hence their closures are related.
  have hIncl : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (A : Set X)) :=
    closure_mono hP1
  -- Put the two inclusions together to get equality.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `closure (interior A)` is certainly contained in `univ`.
    intro _ _; trivial
  · -- Using `hClA` and `hIncl`, we have `univ ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
    have : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := by
      simpa [hClA] using hIncl
    exact this

theorem closure_subset_closure_interior_of_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  simpa [closure_closure] using (closure_mono hP1)
